This place has been in Cleburne for around 25 years though I had never stopped in. It is locally owned and always seemed to be busy, friends recommended the burgers but said rest of food, at best, mediocre. The staff was very disorganized and I finally grabbed a menu and seated myself. I was brought chips and salsa. . I did not try the salsa, chips were store bought. My server was pleasant and made sure I had everything. I ordered the cheeseburger, I did not find anything special about it, though It was huge, good if you have an appetite. It Was lathered with mustard on both sides, so it was all I tasted. Unfortunately the only 'cheese' offered is American processed cheese product. The Fries were greasy, but tasted good. Watching orders going out, it was apparent that very little of what was on the plates were made in house. Atmosphere: brightly lit fluorescent lighting. Very loud, not from music but from diners, all surfaces were hard so nothing to dampen the noise. Restaurant was not kept up and showed its age. Almost Everyone seemed to know each other. The owner made the rounds chatting for long periods of time with specific diners. Overall,  the food really is nothing special but the regulars seemed to enjoy themselves.
